theorem
(((Y c= X & Y <> ( {} )) & H is_point_conv_on X) implies (H is_point_conv_on Y & ( ( lim (H,X) ) | Y ) = ( lim (H,Y) )))
proof
assume that
A1: Y c= X
and
A2: Y <> ( {} )
and
A3: H is_point_conv_on X;
consider f such that A4: X = ( dom f ) and A5: (for x holds (x in X implies (for p holds (p > ( 0 ) implies (ex k st (for n holds (n >= k implies ( abs ( ( ( H . n ) . x ) - ( f . x ) ) ) < p))))))) by A3,CKB33:def 1;
A6:now
take g = ( f | Y );
thus A7: Y = ( dom g ) by A1,A4,RELAT_1:62;
let x;
assume A8: x in Y;
let p;
assume p > ( 0 );
then consider k such that A9: (for n holds (n >= k implies ( abs ( ( ( H . n ) . x ) - ( f . x ) ) ) < p)) by A1,A5,A8;
take k;
let n;
assume n >= k;
then ( abs ( ( ( H . n ) . x ) - ( f . x ) ) ) < p by A9;
hence ( abs ( ( ( H . n ) . x ) - ( g . x ) ) ) < p by A7,A8,FUNCT_1:47;
end;
X common_on_dom H by A3,CKB33:def 1;
then Y common_on_dom H by A1,A2,CKB40:1;
hence A10: H is_point_conv_on Y by A6,CKB33:def 1;
A11:now
let x;
assume A12: x in ( dom ( ( lim (H,X) ) | Y ) );
then A13: x in ( ( dom ( lim (H,X) ) ) /\ Y ) by RELAT_1:61;
then A14: x in ( dom ( lim (H,X) ) ) by XBOOLE_0:def 4;
x in Y by A13,XBOOLE_0:def 4;
then A15: x in ( dom ( lim (H,Y) ) ) by A10,CKB37:def 1;
thus ( ( ( lim (H,X) ) | Y ) . x ) = ( ( lim (H,X) ) . x ) by A12,FUNCT_1:47
.= ( lim ( H # x ) ) by A3,A14,CKB37:def 1
.= ( ( lim (H,Y) ) . x ) by A10,A15,CKB37:def 1;
end;
( dom ( lim (H,X) ) ) = X by A3,CKB37:def 1;
then ( ( dom ( lim (H,X) ) ) /\ Y ) = Y by A1,XBOOLE_1:28;
then ( dom ( ( lim (H,X) ) | Y ) ) = Y by RELAT_1:61;
then ( dom ( ( lim (H,X) ) | Y ) ) = ( dom ( lim (H,Y) ) ) by A10,CKB37:def 1;
hence thesis by A11,PARTFUN1:5;
end;
